##See the sanitation workers during the outbreak

Micro Signal Anti

Features A2n, Anti-2019-ncov. A group of folk volunteers whose main work is to popularize science and dispel rumors.

Not An easy thing to do

"Silent City Beautician" , is the public praise to the sanitation workers, they quietly maintain the city's appearance in the first line of clean. By 2013, there were about 50,000 sanitation workers in the city. Sanitation workers are generally over 50 years old, have low levels of education and wages, and do not have close working relationships.

In this case, they still have to work at the risk of infection. According to statistics, there are more than million sanitation workers in Shanghai. How to hold their bottom line of safety has aroused Wu Hongyue's concern. She and her reading group saw two teams, "mask Beijing" and "Mask Shenzhen" , launch a project to raise money for sanitation workers to buy anti-epidemic supplies, so they want to do similar work in Shanghai. January 27, "Mask Shanghai" fund-raising assistance program was officially launched, on the one hand to recruit volunteers all over Shanghai field survey of sanitation workers, write related reports, on the other hand began to look everywhere mask and disinfection supplies channel.

On March 6, "Mask Shanghai" volunteers
Western union sanitation co-ordinates the distribution of masks in Changning District

Wu described the event as "not an easy little thing. ". Said is a small matter, because "mask Shanghai" can donate masks for the thousands of Shanghai sanitation workers on the job, almost a drop in the bucket, just a little help. They could buy less than a typical sanitation facility needs in a week, but they're doing everything they can to help. In order to find a scarce supply of masks, "mask Shanghai" contact channels around the world. In the Middle East, they "visited" sources in Israel, sought out hebrew-speaking classmates for certification and negotiated with manufacturers; in Africa, Wu Hongyue and his friends searched through several sources from Nigeria to South Africa; When a Vietnamese supplier in Southeast Asia threw out some Vietnamese documents that looked like a certificate of competency under their scrutiny, she immediately called in a Vietnamese speaking friend, successfully "debunked" the truth of this qualification certificate: It is only the qualification certificate of the cloth used to make the mask, not the qualification certificate of the mask..

During the campaign, Wu mobilized nearly all the volunteers he could reach to assist in the verification, to ensure that each item was safe for workers to use. After going through a rigorous approval process, they were matched with two trusted suppliers in more than 100 of the mask channels they had contacted. Considering that the "mask Shanghai" team is mainly just entering the community of students, to be able to integrate so many information channels to complete the procurement review work, it is indeed not easy to practice.

Hard way to start a business

The team's energy also surprised Wu Hongyue: In early February, when resources were busiest, she would stay up until midnight every day and throw any uncertain questions into the group, a friend would text her back and offer advice.

As it turned out, Wu Hongyue felt that the outcome of the event had exceeded their expectations. As of March 7, "Mask Shanghai" raised a total of 40,587.99 yuan, and donated more than 10,000 masks and anti-epidemic items such as disinfection alcohol for several sanitation offices, and distributed materials on the spot. Looking back on this period of volunteer work, Wu Hongyue has an interesting word to describe it: hardships. This is not only because of the procurement, research and docking process of the arduous, everyone's eager expectations also brought pressure to the team. Since the announcement, more and more eager volunteers have flocked to the forum -- as if to explain their work to their friends and announce their progress.

Western union sanitation in Changning District thanks 'mask Shanghai'

She felt that the "mask Shanghai" team was lucky: On the one hand, the sponsor had transparent management, regularly announcing the progress of donations and material purchases every day, and accepting inquiries and discussions from the group; on the other hand, shanghai Lianquan Fund also helped "mask Shanghai" successfully completed the regularization work. As the initial fund-raising has exceeded million yuan, and they lack the public fund-raising qualifications, Wu Hongyue contact relevant organizations everywhere in order to rely on the foundation. After asking around, she met an enthusiastic person in a group who worked for the United Way Foundation. After knowing the situation of the project, the other side not only agreed with them to join the United Advice, but also waived a part of the management fee, to ensure that the "mask Shanghai" donations can be used as fully as possible for epidemic prevention. In addition, the Celtic F.C. has donated nearly 2,000 masks to them, in part to supplement the scarce supply.

A life with no right answer

Of course, there is more than goodwill along the way, and there are some doubts. Wu still doesn't tell her family about the program -- as if it was a waste of time, since she was an undergraduate helping children in a village in the city, and it's not gonNA help you with your education or your career. Wu Hongyue can only use the argument that "social practice is helpful to credit evaluation" to relieve the pressure from his family. "Why would a group of students want to help a sanitation company worry about what they're supposed to do? " Asked another, after learning about their project. These doubts did occasionally cause some stress within the team, but fortunately they did not prevent the project from going forward.

Although the "minority" question did not let Wu Hongyue retreat, but she can also feel that the community's awareness of public welfare is still lacking. The rapid development of the economy, taking up a lot of personal time, to a certain extent, will also weaken people's enthusiasm to participate in public affairs. As a youth who had public welfare experience at the grass-roots level, Hong Yue had a deep understanding of "the false myth of rising class" . "The market promises that as long as the economy continues to grow and resources become available, the dream of rising class can be realized by hard work and individuals can be freer than in traditional societies. But as I watched hardworking children drop out of primary school and head to the labor market in the village where I once volunteered, I could only see the futility of imagining the future in the fast fashion mobile apps. I always feel that the myth of the struggle to change fate is being shattered."

A village in Kunming where Wu Hongyue once volunteered
The children play and study together around the multimedia equipment

"For example, I once met a couple of sisters in the village who went to work in the village shop after sixth grade for family reasons. Of course, they had their own ideas about whether to study or earn money -- as if she wanted to continue her studies, while her sister wanted to earn money to support her family and lead a relatively free life. But in the end, they gave up their studies because of the pressure of their families. The next time I saw them was at a food stand in the village. The two of them ate with a shudder of sound, and declared to me that they seemed to be doing just fine

"To be honest, it's hard to say which life choices are 'right' . When those children have not entered the society, they even hope to grow up to be engaged in the occupation of their parents, even if it is just a common construction workers, a vegetable peddler... for them, this seems to be a very natural way of life, and may even be more interesting than the whole day in front of the English teaching do not understand. Although their parents often expect them to change their fate through reading, never to live their own poor days now, hoping that they can rely on reading to get ahead. But many of them will also feel happy to have a family like their parents, and there will be a lot of estrangement between the two generations, we were all silent for a moment. The plight of those at the bottom is not just resource-based; it also further impedes their development in the broader public life. This means that when they can't break through their resource constraints, they see the option of settling as the most normal and acceptable option.

A village in Kunming where Wu Hongyue once volunteered
The children played together on the concrete playground

A great distance

Of course, in addition to these external environment does not understand and difficulties, in the face of sanitation workers, Wu Hongyue will also have some barriers. Many sanitation workers do not use smartphones, and most do not use them at work, making it extremely difficult for the survey team to keep in touch with them. Living Environment and habits of the huge difference, so "mask Shanghai" can only donate some epidemic prevention materials, can not provide them with more psychological support.

"although I've studied 'new worker and Peasant Culture, ' I've Read Lu Tu and Paul Willis's books on worker living conditions, and I've seen Ken loach's films about the conditions of couriers in a part-time economy. But when I did get into it, I felt that there was a distance between what I felt on camera and on paper and the state of the living community. "while we believe they should have their own culture, it's not easy to get into their conversation quickly. "

One of Wu Hongyue's favorite books
Prison Notebooks by Antonio Gramsci, an Italian Communist

The phenomenon of "cultural hegemony" is discussed in detail in the book
Reveals how, since ancient times, the lower classes
Never had a portrait painted of himself
It's a cultural issue that always allows those in power to dress up as they see fit

In this Shanghai epidemic prevention activity, in addition to the "mask Shanghai" Group of hot-blooded young people concerned about the situation of sanitation workers, Huaxia Insurance Shanghai Branch also gave epidemic prevention insurance to 58,000 sanitation workers in the urban area. Wu Hongyue sincerely hopes that in the future, the groups with little voice will not only receive more attention and help from the society, whether in daily management or in disaster emergency response, there are also channels for participation in the public system (such as communities and companies) -- as in the early "crowd control" campaigns against infectious diseases such as schistosomiasis and the plague. On the contrary, without such a public system that accommodates different classes, our daily life is only concerned with the options given to us by popular culture, especially the small circles of cyberspace, then we'll only be able to reach people with similar levels of consumption and tastes. Groups as disparate as sanitation workers may be directly out of the reach of young students. This state of affairs goes without saying that understanding, even communication will encounter difficulties. Only in real life space to build a platform for joint participation, consultation and governance, social strata, including grass-roots groups can begin to slowly contact and integration, create a real culture of the people.

Epilogue
An interesting couplet seen by Wu Hongyue in a village
I hope that one day there will be true equality and freedom in the world
Including the workers and peasants who are still poor

During those conversations, I began to feel that the screen gave no hint of the coolness of her names, but instead, the warmth of a perpetually marginal crowd stirred in her chest. At this point, i am reminded of the words of the 2018 conference commemorating the 200th anniversary of Marxism's birth: "[ Marxism ] has shown man the way to leap from the realm of necessity to the realm of freedom, and the way to freedom and liberation for the people. " I think, these poor workers are certainly entitled to be part of the Kingdom of liberty and one of the protagonists in the path of socialist construction. Although they still have a weak situation that needs to be solved urgently, every socialist striver should shoulder the heavy responsibility of solving this problem together with the passionate young people of "mask Shanghai" , let them feel the care of the society.

Just as the rising sun will burst the first fish belly white on the horizon, we always believe that this The Hours is pregnant with hope, a socialist dream that belongs to the community of human destiny.

Before the intervention of professional agencies, they help to help the epidemic areas to tide over the difficulties. Why are these volunteer groups created, and how do they ensure their uniqueness and relevance? What difficulties have you encountered and what changes have you experienced in your volunteer activities? After professional organizations gradually take over the right to speak, how to reflect on the meaning of their actions?

A2n depth project "line of thinking"
Will Talk to the members of these voluntary groups, take you through one by one is acting and thinking of the "I" , understand "we" have been and are on the way.
I'll see you next time!
